  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , RF-powered CRNs with multiple STs are studied. Similar to [CITATION_2] , the authors formulate an optimization problem to find the trade-off between data backscatter time and energy harvesting time to maximize network throughput. The authors demonstrate that the objective function, i.e., the network throughput, is concave. Thus, there exists a globally optimal trade-off between data backscatter and energy harvesting time, and also time sharing among STs. Lu et al. [CITATION_3] introduce a hybrid transmitter that integrates ambient backscatter with wireless-powered communication capability to improve transmission performance. The structure of this hybrid transmitter is shown in Fig. 15 .",
